THE SENATE
S.B. NO.
THIRTY-THIRD LEGISLATURE, 2025
STATE OF HAWAII
CD. 1
A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO CAPITAL IMPROVEMENT PROJECTS AT STATE SMALL BOAT
HARBORS AND STATE PARKS.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that state small boat
2 harbors and state parks serve as vital hubs of recreation and
3 tourism for residents and visitors. However, facilities at
4 these locations suffer from significant wear due to constant use
5 and lack of timely repair, maintenance, and renovation.
6 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to:
7 (1) Provide the division of boating and ocean recreation
8 and the division of state parks the flexibility to
9 undertake certain necessary repairs and renovations
10 for existing facilities without prior legislative or
11 gubernatorial authorization;
12 (2) Establish a notification protocol to ensure that the
13 legislature is informed of expenditures before they
14 occur; and
15 (3) Establish semiannual reporting requirements to the
16 legislature to ensure transparency and accountability.
