1 SECTION 2. Section 103-7, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 "§103-7 Capital improvements; authorizations for;
4 emergency repairs or reconstruction, [exeeptien-:-] exceptions;
5 small state boat harbors and state parks; report. (a) All
6 capital improvement projects requiring the use of general funds,
7 special funds, general obligation bonds, and revenue bonds of
8 the State, except projects covered by subsection (b) and
9 chapter 41D_j_ shall require authorization by the legislature and
10 the governor.
11 (b) Capital improvement projects for state small boat
12 harbors and state parks for the repair, renovation, or
13 replacement of existing facilities, including dredging, shall
14 not require authorization from the legislature or governor;
IS provided that an expenditure made under this subsection shall:
16 (1) Be strictly limited to major repairs, renovations, or
17 ‘ replacements; and
18 (2) Not be used for yie const£Uct2^on of jiew fa£ilJ^t£es or
19 appurtenances.
