1 A department managing an expenditure made under this subsection
2 shall issue a written notice to the legislature no later than
3 fourteen business days before authorizing the expenditure.
4 (c) The department of land and natural resources shall
5 submit a semiannual report to the legislature that includes an
6 account of the total semiannual expenditures incurred for any
7 expenditure made under subsection (b); types of repairs,
8 renovations, or replacements completed; justification for each
9 expenditure; status of ongoing or planned projects; and detailed
10 accounting of all capital improvement projects. The reports
11 shall be due no later than June 30 and December 31 of each
12 year. "
13 SECTION 3. Statutory material to be repealed is bracketed
14 and stricken. New statutory material is underscored.
15 SECTION 4. This Act shall take effect on July 1, 2026;
16 provided that five years after the effective date of this Act,
17 this Act shall be repealed and section 103-7, Hawaii Revised
18 Statutes, shall be reenacted in the form in which it read on the
19 day prior to the effective date of this Act.
